{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4f7e3426-fcb3-4cbd-94e7-057515e22f99","content":"Here's the plan and architecture for your RAG-based Q&A feature:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐       ┌────────────────┐\n│  Markdown  │──────▶│  Ingestion Svc   │──────▶│  Vector Store  │\n│  Docs/     │       │  (chunk + embed) │       │  (in-memory or │\n└────────────┘       └──────────────────┘       │   Qdrant/PG)   │\n                                                 └───────┬────────┘\n                                                         │\n┌────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐                │\n│  User Q&A  │──────▶│  Query Endpoint  │◀───────────────┘\n│  POST /ask │       │  retrieve + LLM  │\n└────────────┘       └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Components\n\n| Layer | Responsibility |\n|-------|---------------|\n| **Document Ingestion** | Read `Docs/*.md`, split into chunks (~300–500 tokens), generate embeddings via OpenAI/Azure OpenAI, store in vector DB |\n| **Vector Store** | Stores chunk text + embedding vector. Start with `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` (new in .NET 10) or an in-memory store; swap to Qdrant/pgvector later |\n| **Query Endpoint** | `POST /ask` — embed the question, retrieve top-K similar chunks, pass them as context to an LLM, return the grounded answer |\n| **LLM Integration** | Use `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` (the new abstraction in .NET 10) to call OpenAI/Azure OpenAI for both embeddings and chat completions |\n\n---\n\n## Ingestion Pipeline\n\n1. **Load** — enumerate `Docs/*.md`\n2. **Chunk** — split by markdown headings or sliding window (~400 tokens, 50-token overlap)\n3. **Embed** — call embedding model (e.g. `text-embedding-3-small`)\n4. **Store** — upsert `{ id, source_file, chunk_text, vector }` into vector store\n\nExpose as `POST /ingest` (or run on startup).\n\n---\n\n## Query Flow (`POST /ask`)\n\n1. Embed the user question\n2. Vector similarity search → top 5 chunks\n3. Build prompt: system message + retrieved chunks + user question\n4. Call chat completion → return answer + source references\n\n---\n\n## Suggested NuGet Packages\n\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI` — unified LLM abstraction\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.Abstractions` — vector store abstraction\n- A concrete vector store package (in-memory for dev, Qdrant/pgvector for prod)\n\n---\n\n## Project Structure (proposed)\n\n```\nProductQA/\n├── Controllers/\n│   └── AskController.cs        # POST /ask\n├── Ingestion/\n│   ├── DocumentLoader.cs       # reads Docs/*.md\n│   ├── TextChunker.cs          # markdown-aware chunking\n│   └── IngestionService.cs     # orchestrates load→chunk→embed→store\n├── Retrieval/\n│   └── RetrievalService.cs     # embed query → vector search → return chunks\n├── Generation/\n│   └── AnswerGenerator.cs      # builds prompt, calls LLM\n├── Models/\n│   └── Dtos.cs                 # AskRequest, AskResponse, ChunkRecord\n├── Docs/                       # existing markdown files\n├── Program.cs\n└── appsettings.json            # API keys, model names, chunk settings\n```\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to implement this, or do you want to adjust the plan first (e.g., choice of vector store, chunking strategy, or auth)?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5f0d892c-8924-41be-b852-7b1ac9f70473","outputTokens":959,"requestId":"5C32:A2F50:5EDBFB:6E3F32:69FAA53E"},"id":"358c9aaa-31f6-4944-a49a-fd93563c7c52","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:20:01.639Z","parentId":"5d9e7619-4ea5-4959-83ec-b4dfcd97218b"}
